{"author":{"id":"2329d242a564d858d1460ecfa8faffbd4bbf14caa989b5b8c6fcd76a16aedb80"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1612021200,"nonce":"caz8uI8W2mU9SL+5LV7ns9VudeA=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU3OTc0NDgzNDY=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3451","origin":"github"},"title":"extract_genomic_dna tool requires genome and query to have dbkey even if genome is from history","message":"The [extract_genomic_dna](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/tree/master/tools/extract_genomic_dna) tool extracts a region from a genomic contig, with the region being described in some interval format. It currently requires ([1](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/master/tools/extract_genomic_dna/extract_genomic_dna.xml#L41), [2](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/master/tools/extract_genomic_dna/extract_genomic_dna.xml#L63)) a dbkey to be associated with both the interval file and the genomic contigs. While this aids in validation, it is not actually used in processing: the dbkey is only used ([3](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/master/tools/extract_genomic_dna/extract_genomic_dna.xml#L9)) for naming the output sequence and in error messages.\n\nI am opening this issue to start a discussion on whether this constraint should be removed. \n\nPro: \n* it would allow using the tool with \"plain FASTA\" that is not associated with a genome known to Galaxy\n\nCon:\n* it would remove the validation that ensures the interval matches the genome (although this validation is also, arguably, performed by checking chromosome name in interval against chromosome name in genome)\n* encouraging data in Galaxy to be associated with genome builds is a good thing, and making this optional would remove an incentive\n\nI'm tagging some notable contributors to this tool: @gregvonkuster @mvdbeek","files":null}]}